data.chText: （尤指在社交场合）使窘迫，使尴尬
data.enText: to make sb feel shy, awkward or ashamed, especially in a social situation

data.chText: 她询问我的私生活使我感到很尴尬。
data.enText: Her questions about my private life embarrassed me.

data.chText: 我并没想当着他的朋友吻他而使他感到难堪。
data.enText: I didn't want to embarrass him by kissing him in front of his friends.

data.chText: 夜里在走廊上遇见陌生男人使她感到很不好意思。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: It embarrassed her to meet strange men in the corridor at night.

data.chText: 使困惑；使为难；使陷入困境
data.enText: to cause problems or difficulties for sb

data.chText: 这个发言是故意为难首相。
data.enText: The speech was deliberately designed to embarrass the prime minister.

simple_means.memory_skill: em 进入…之中；包围 + barrass 套子 → 被套子套住 → 难堪

tr: hinder or prevent the progress or accomplishment of
example: His brother blocked him at every turn

value.def: If something or someone embarrasses you, they make you feel shy or ashamed.

example.tran: 他因自己的笨拙而感到尴尬。

example.ex: It embarrassed him that he had no idea of what was going on.
example.tran: 对所发生的事情一无所知，这让他很难堪。

value.def: If something embarrasses a public figure such as a politician or an organization such as a political party, it causes problems for them.

example.ex: The Republicans are trying to embarrass the president by thwarting his economic program...
example.tran: 共和党人企图通过阻挠总统的经济计划使其难堪。

example.ex: The Government has been embarrassed by the affair.
example.tran: 这件事给政府出了难题。

value.tran: 使（公众人物、组织等）难堪;给…出难题

usage_note.note: Be careful with the spelling of this word.
